# COMMON WINDOWS APPLICATION PATHS

# Microsoft Office
# - Word: C:\Program Files\Microsoft Office\root\Office16\WINWORD.EXE
# - Excel: C:\Program Files\Microsoft Office\root\Office16\EXCEL.EXE
# - PowerPoint: C:\Program Files\Microsoft Office\root\Office16\POWERPNT.EXE
# - Outlook: C:\Program Files\Microsoft Office\root\Office16\OUTLOOK.EXE

# Development Tools
# - Visual Studio Code: C:\Users\[YourUsername]\AppData\Local\Programs\Microsoft VS Code\Code.exe
# - Visual Studio: C:\Program Files\Microsoft Visual Studio\2022\Community\Common7\IDE\devenv.exe
# - Git Bash: C:\Program Files\Git\bin\bash.exe
# - Node.js: C:\Program Files\nodejs\node.exe

# Communication
# - Discord: C:\Users\[YourUsername]\AppData\Local\Discord\Update.exe --processStart Discord.exe
# - Slack: C:\Users\[YourUsername]\AppData\Local\Slack\Slack.exe
# - Telegram: C:\Users\[YourUsername]\AppData\Roaming\Telegram Desktop\Telegram.exe

# Media & Entertainment
# - Spotify: C:\Users\[YourUsername]\AppData\Roaming\Spotify\Spotify.exe
# - VLC Media Player: C:\Program Files\VideoLAN\VLC\vlc.exe
# - Blender: C:\Program Files\Blender Foundation\Blender 3.6\blender.exe

# Utilities
# - 7-Zip: C:\Program Files\7-Zip\7zFM.exe
# - WinRAR: C:\Program Files\WinRAR\WinRAR.exe

# FINDING APPLICATION PATHS
# 
# Method 1: Right-click shortcut -> Properties -> Look at "Target"
# Method 2: Open Settings > Apps > Apps & features > Find app > Click > Related settings > Open file location
# Method 3: Use Windows Search to find the app, right-click and select "Open file location"
# Method 4: In Command Prompt, use "where appname" (e.g., "where python")

# TIPS FOR VOICE TRIGGERS
# - Keep triggers short and distinct (2-3 words ideal)
# - Avoid similar-sounding triggers
# - Use common phrases you can remember
# - Example: Instead of "launch that google application", use "open browser"
